{"id": "duc04-testb-45:9#27", "contents": "FBI agents have begun questioning relatives of the victims of the August 7 U.S. Embassy bombing in Nairobi, Kenya, as well as those who were seriously injured, at the request of the U.S. Attorney's office for the Southern District of New York. The bombing resulted in the loss of 213 lives, including 12 Americans, and injured 5,400 people. A nearly simultaneous bombing of the U.S. Embassy in Dar es Salaam, Tanzania, claimed 11 lives and injured 85 people, with no American casualties. The questioning aims to gather recorded testimony for the prosecution's use in the pre-sentencing phase of the trials of the six men indicted in connection with the attack."}
